The paper deals with network steganography, which involves hiding information within network transmissions. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a framework and metric for evaluating the creativity of hiding techniques, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of existing countermeasures, which falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
